  "texts": [
    "For instance, in a recent agent benchmark (Mialon et al., 2023), even GPT4 falls short with a success rate of 14%, while humans effortlessly exceed 92%.",
    "Empowering agents to effectively address real-world tasks is challenging, arising from difficulties in both benchmark and methodological perspectives.",
    "From a benchmark perspective, we have witnessed lots of agent-related benchmarks in the passing year, covering domains like web manipulation (Yao et al., 2022), gaming (Wang et al., 2023a), and software control (Li et al., 2023).",
    "However, the evaluation metrics in current benchmarks often lack the granularity needed to accurately reflect the incremental progress of agents.",
    "In complex multistep tasks, even if an agent fails to achieve the ultimate targets, it might successfully accomplish some of the subtasks."
  ],
